CONCURRENCY is the composition of independently executing process, while PARALLELISM is the simultaneosly execution
of computations. CONCURRENCY is about DEALING WITH LOTS OF THINGS AT ONCE
PARALLELISM is about DOING WITH LOTS OF THINGS AT ONCE.

CONCURRENCY: doing many things, but only one at a time "multitasking"

vi du dien hinh cua CONCURRENCY: mot nguoi chi co the noi chuyen, XONG ROI uong 1 xiu nuoc, XONG ROI lai noi chuyen,
XONG ROI lai uong nuoc, v.v

PARALLELISM: doing many things at a time:

vi du dien hinh: mot nguoi VUA noi chuyen VUA uong nuoc => bi SAC